# Flashcard App Development Rules

## [Before Starting Task] [bst] [1]
- Review and understand the user's requirements completely
- Think step-by-step and describe your plan
- Identify any areas of uncertainty
- Ask clarifying questions if needed
- Confirm understanding before proceeding

## [During Planning] [dp] [2]
- Break down the task into clear steps
- Consider edge cases and potential issues
- Plan for error handling
- Consider performance implications
- Document the approach

## [During Implementation] [di] [3]
- Follow best practices and DRY principles
- Write bug-free, functional code
- Keep documentation updated
- Consider code maintainability
- Test as you go

## [Before Completing] [bc] [4]
- Verify all requirements are met
- Check code is complete and functional
- Ensure documentation is updated
- Review for potential issues
- Confirm with user before finalizing

## [When Uncertain] [wu] [5]
- If you think there might not be a correct answer, say so
- If you don't know the answer, say so
- Don't guess or make assumptions
- Ask for clarification
- Be honest about limitations

## [During Code Review] [cr] [6]
- Check for unused code
- Verify comments are current
- Ensure consistent code style
- Look for potential improvements
- Validate error handling 

## [Documentation and Cleanup] [dc] [7]
### Maintain documentation
  - Keep API documentation up to date
  - Update setup instructions
  - Document new features
  - Add troubleshooting guides
### Code cleanup
  - Remove unused files
  - Remove commented-out code
  - Update outdated comments
  - Standardize code style
